The paper deals with the problem of detecting counterfeit apps, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to generate embeddings for images, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques such as content embeddings and combining embeddings, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of a large dataset of apps, which involves data mining and software engineering techniques (cs.SE).
